# Testing

## Setup

- Runner: **Vitest 2** (Vite-native)
- Environment: `jsdom`
- Globals: enabled (`describe`, `it`, `expect`, `beforeEach` etc. — no imports needed)
- Matchers: `@testing-library/jest-dom/vitest` (loaded in `src/test/setup.ts`)
- Cleanup: auto via `afterEach(() => cleanup())` in setup file

## File location

```
src/
├── App.tsx
└── test/
    ├── setup.ts              ← jest-dom + auto cleanup
    └── App.test.tsx          ← smoke tests
```

## Patterns

### Component smoke test

```tsx
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import { Card } from '../components/Card';

describe('Card', () => {
  it('renders title and children', () => {
    render(<Card title="Hi"><p>Body</p></Card>);
    expect(screen.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Hi' })).toBeInTheDocument();
    expect(screen.getByText('Body')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

### User interaction

```tsx
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';

it('submits the form', async () => {
  const onSubmit = vi.fn();
  render(<Form onSubmit={onSubmit} />);
  await userEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /submit/i }));
  expect(onSubmit).toHaveBeenCalledOnce();
});
```

## What to test

- ✅ Component renders expected text/elements
- ✅ User interactions (click, type, submit)
- ✅ Conditional rendering (loading, error, empty states)
- ✅ Accessibility — queries by role, name, label
- ❌ Implementation details (internal state, private functions)
- ❌ Snapshot tests (low signal-to-noise)
- ❌ Trivial getters

## Coverage

Run: `npm run test:coverage` → text + HTML report in `coverage/`.

Configured in `vitest.config.ts`:
- Provider: v8
- Excludes: `node_modules/`, `src/test/`, `*.d.ts`, `*.config.*`